  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved Protection through Provision of Emergency Shelter and Psychosocial Support to IDPs and Host Communities in Barsalogho and Djibo Communes</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following recurrent violence in Burkina Faso, resulting in internally displaced people (IDPs) and host communities coexisting in dire conditions in the Centre-Nord and Sahel regions of Burkina Faso, IOM&apos;s project aims at bringing life-saving assistance to 12,203 vulnerable IDPs and host communities through emergency shelter and protection activities in the Djibo and Barsaiogho communes.  1,029 households will thus receive Sahelian-designed emergency shelters. Protection mobile teams will bring assistance to 5,000 IDPs and host communities through 96 mental and psychosocial support community-based activities and adequate referral for cases needing individual follow-up.</narrative>
  </description>
